I Wanna Escape Into My Mind

Completed
Delicious Fruit
2220
720min 2026-01-18 20:54 Yes
THXel Rating
9/10
THXel Difficulty
57/100
DF Rating
9.1/10
DF Difficulty
49.8/100
Comment
I Wanna Escape Into My Mind is a really special fangame to me. The fact that it runs in 16:9 thanks to the Unity engine already makes it feel completely different, and it looks great right away.
I love the level design and all the characters, who are also insanely well animated. The overall difficulty feels solid, and for me the stages are often harder than the bosses. Still, the boss fights were a ton of fun. And the story is genuinely deep.
Spoiler
One thing that (like many others) sometimes bothers me is the music. Dont get me wrong, there are a lot of real bangers in this game. But at times it feels like its just screaming into your ears. I can imagine thats even intentional, since it fits the theme of trying to escape your own mind and the music is supposed to put you under pressure. But just screaming isnt the same as a tense, nerve-grinding atmosphere. Maybe it works at first, but after a while it becomes more annoying than unsettling.

Comment
Wannafest 22 is currently my #2 favorite fangame. Its insanely creative, with such a great variety of games it really feels like a retro game marathon across the whole I Wanna Be The Guy universe.
There are so many cool childhood elements in here, and I love how it actually includes the signature mechanics of each main protagonist. The fact that they even carry over the HUD from the respective games is just genius.
Spoiler
And the 3D sections? Honestly super surprising I didnt expect them to work this well, but the execution is really impressive.
Awesome game. I always have a great time coming back to it.

50/100
DF Rating
8.3/10
DF Difficulty
44.1/100
Comment
I had a lot of fun with this game. I like games with many WTF moments and it has some really cool gimmicks. I had to look something up at one point because, as a beginner I don't have the knowledge to figure it out on my own.
Here and there, I had a bit of trouble understanding some of the memes, but thats also part of what makes the WTF moments fun.
Thank you for finally letting me visit the Chicken Nugget Universe and that flamingo earworm. It makes my life a bit happier
The final boss was super cool and really creative. This game isnt too difficult and you can play through it on a relaxing Sunday.
Bossfight
Spoiler
I found the Miku fight a bit monotonous in terms of the attacks. For example even just having different colored fruits would be an upgrade.

Level
Spoiler
The part with the Super Mario game and the various mini-bosses was a bit annoying in terms of the path. The bosses were cool especially the Goomba but the overworld was a bit frustrating with the endless invisible blocks. Also the stop-motion with the Boo ghost was really hard to follow since the photo was always in a different position. Maybe that was part of the joke, but for me, it was eye strain

I Wanna Be The Boshy

Completed
Delicious Fruit YouTube
>9000
>9000min 2026-01-16 20:55 Yes
THXel Rating
9/10
THXel Difficulty
83/100
DF Rating
8.0/10
DF Difficulty
66.7/100
Comment
I Wanna Be the Boshy was my very first I Wanna Be The Guy fangame. I originally got inspired by watching the runner Witwix speedrun it at GDQ. Back then I didnt even know I Wanna Be the Guy existed, and I was absolutely blown away: how can a game be that insanely hard, and how can someone clear it that fast?
So many moments had me going WTF is happening?! and thats exactly what made me want to try it myself. But when I actually started playing I didnt even get past the first boss (Kirby). After what felt like 30 hours, I quit.
Fast forward five years: I started streaming on Twitch, gave it another shot, and finally beat it for the first time. And then I even ended up speedrunning it which younger me wouldve thought was impossible.
